  "text": "As our model checking approach constructs an observer (defined in the next two sections) for the negation \u00ac\u03c6 of the formula \u03c6 under consideration and the observer uses the strong semantics to accept paths of the observed system, we can find all the finite paths in the system that violate \u03c6 and are informative bad prefixes for \u03c6. However, observe that some safety formulae do not have informative bad prefixes. As an example (taken from [CITATION_1] ), the LTL safety formula",
